<TEXT>
<P>
Eight scientific adventurers packed the last of their food and arctic gear
Monday and tested their high-tech equipment before setting out to climb Mt.
McKinley and find out exactly how high North America's tallest peak really is.
</P>
<P>
"Everyone says we better make the mountain larger," Jeff Yates, assistant
project coordinator, said.
</P>
<P>
